### 1. Definitions

- "Project" means the code, configuration, documentation, UI text, images, icons, samples, generated files, and derivative works contained in this repository.
- "Commercial Use" means use for sale, subscription, advertising revenue, commissioned delivery, paid support, license fees, or any other profit-seeking purpose.
- "Trademarks" means `AA-Maker`, `Elegg Retro CRT`, `elegg.jp`, logos, app icons, service names, domain names, and any confusingly similar identifiers. Ordinary functional UI icons are not Trademarks unless they are used as identifying marks of the Project.

### 2. Grant

The copyright holder grants you a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to use, view, copy, modify, and redistribute the Project for non-commercial purposes only.

Any public derivative work must satisfy all of the following:

- keep this LICENSE and the NOTICE file
- keep the original copyright notices
- avoid misleading changes to the original LICENSE, NOTICE, and copyright notices, even when adding copyright notices, change notices, or third-party notices for derivative works
- remain clearly distinguishable from the Project
- avoid suggesting that it is the official, successor, or endorsed version of the Project

Keeping or publishing a fork, clone, or branch for issues, pull requests, review, testing, or contribution preparation is not treated as public redistribution of an unmodified copy, provided that it is non-commercial and is not presented as an alternative distribution of the Project.

### 3. Restrictions

The following are prohibited:

- Commercial Use
- Public redistribution of unmodified copies or copies that are substantially identical to the Project
- Unauthorized use of the Trademarks
- Impersonation using the Project name, logos, appearance, or description
- Removing original copyright notices, this LICENSE, or the NOTICE file, or altering them in a way that misrepresents the original terms

### 4. Third-Party Materials

Third-party code, fonts, images, icons, libraries, and other materials included in the Project remain subject to their own license terms.

### 5. Disclaimer of Warranty

The Project is provided "as is". The copyright holder and contributors make no warranties of any kind, express or implied, including warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.

### 6. Limitation of Liability

The copyright holder and contributors are not liable for any damages arising from the use or inability to use the Project.
